Slice tofu into 12 equal rectangular pieces. Sprinkle salt on both sides of tofu slices. Heat vegetable oil in a large, deep saucepan over medium heat. Dip tofu slices into bowl of beaten egg and fry in hot oil until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Mix soy sauce, green onions, chile peppers, vinegar, sugar, and red pepper flakes together in a small bowl. Dip fried tofu into dipping sauce.